Failing to\nFurnish Sufficient Identifica\ntion or Refusal to Designate\nParty Affiliations; Providing\nfor Changes of Registration and\nPolitical Party Affiliations Be\ntween Registration Periods and\nProviding for the Registration\nof Voters Failing to Register\nfor the Year 195 b for Elections\nSubsequent to the Year 1950:\nand providing for the Notice to\nVoters by the Supervisor of\nRegistration of Their Registra\ntion as Shown on the Registra\ntion Hooks am! Requesting In\nformation pertinent Thereto in\nthe Year 1953 and Every Eight\nYears Thereafter and the Re\nturn Thereof by the Voters and i\nthe Penalty for failure to Re- j\nturn Said Notice with the In\nformation Requested; Provid\ning That All Registration of\nVoters Heretofore Had in Mon\nroe County, Florida Shall Be\n<opie Void on and After the\nFirst Monda.v in January, 1950:\n'Providing for the Adoption anil\nCtilization of Supplemental\nR9-ord Forms by the Super\nvisor of Registration: Provid\ning for the Furnishing of Reg- j\nAafration Blanks by the Secre\ntary of State and the Herman\neut Regi.st.-atiqn Binders by\nthe County Commissioners;:and\n4FM9pealLng All Laws or Parts\notjLaws Whether Genera) or\nSj>*i ial in Conflict With This\nat Kev West. Florida, this j\n9*b #a v of April A. D. 1949.\nFRANK BE\n0 FRANK BENTLEY, j\nChairman. Board of County\nCommissioners. Monroe\nCounty. Florida.\nmay -l'>. 1949.\nAntiseptic Ointment Aid Fer\nBruises, Burns, Guts\nFor helpful Antiseptic aid in relieving\nP*i\u00ae *d diicoaloit of uteiully\ncaused minor skin irritations and abra\nsuperficial cut*, minor surface\nbuns, sun barn aad bruises. use Grays\nOintment as directed. Medicated te efisf\nnasa m\nChapter 25\nON the last night of Felicity\u2019s\nvisit \u2019to Casa del Mar Susan\ninsisted on giving a party which\nshe called \u201cTippy's coming-out\nparty.\u201d The Horne children. Bur\nton, Garrett and, of course. Ma\nGreen, were all invited and Chal\nmers Thorpe agreed, a trifle\ngrumpily, to come along.\nJust as dinner was over\nthey were lingering over the des\nsert. Susan faced them all. smil\ning brightly, and said. \u201cAnd now.\nI\u2019ve a little announcement to\nmake. Since you\u2019re all my verv\nbest friends. Chalmers and I\nwould like you to be the first to\nknow that we are going to be\nmarried. Isn\u2019t that marvelous?\u2019\nShe beamed down the table at\na Chalmers who stared at her.\nwhite-faced, struck dumb. Fe\nlicity looked swiftly from Susan\u2019s\ncomposed face to Chalmers\u2019\nwhite, startled one. and she. knew\nthat the announcement was a\ncomplete surprise to Chalmers.\nHe sat quite still, staring at\nSusan a moment: and then he\nmade a little helpless gesture ot\nbewilderment, thrust back his\nchair, marched to where she sat,\nlifted her out of her chair and\nkissed her. He looked down at\nher as though he did not know\nthat the others were present,\nand he said, \u201cYou are the most\nmaddening, the most unpredict\nable, the most spoiled creature\nthat ever lived.. But how can 1\ndefend myself against you\u2014when\nI\u2019m so crazy about you?**\n\u201cWell, that\u2019s about the nicest\nthing I could think of to happen,\u201d\nsaid Ma Green happily. \u201cIf there\nwas ever two people that needed\nge,ch other, it\u2019s you.\u201d\nAnd so it turned into a beauti\nful party with all sorts of unex\npected things happening. When it\nwas over, Susan said firmly*\n\u201cGarry, you take Felicity home\nin your car. I\u2019m going to send\nthe others in my car.\u201d\n\u201cThe Rolls-Royce. Susan,\nplease,\u201d said Tippy importantly.\nGarrett drew back and cocked\nan eyebrow at her.\nKey West In\nDavs Gone By\nv\nAS TAX EH FROM FILES\nOF THE CITIZEN OF\nMAY 10. 1339\n(ilinillifinHilSMiniliinfmUHiniMlinTTiiatimninniu\nHenry B. Haskins, assistant su\nperintendent of lighthouses in\nthis district, today returned <fh\nthe tender IVv from an inspection\ntrip at Loggerhead and Rebekah\nShoals lighthouses.\nI Reductions in the WPA force